Package uk.gov.gchq.koryphe.impl.function

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CallMethod
    A CallMethod is a Function that takes a method name and then invokes it.
    Cast<I,O>
    A Cast is a Function that takes an input class and casts it to an output class.
    Concat
    A Concat is a Function that takes in two objects and calls toString on them and concatenates them together.
    Divide
    A Divide is a Function that takes in two Integers and returns the result of dividing the first by the second.
    DivideBy
    A DivideBy is a Function that takes in an Integer and returns the result of dividing this integer by a pre-configured value.
    ExtractKeys<K,V>
    An ExtractKeys is a KorypheFunction which extracts the Set of keys of a provided input Map
    ExtractValue<K,V>
    An ExtractValue is a Function that retrieves the value from a given Map, for the corresponding pre-configured key.
    ExtractValues<K,V>
    An ExtractValues is a KorypheFunction which extracts the Set of values of a provided input Map
    FirstItem<T>
    A FirstItem is a KorypheFunction that returns the first item from a provided Iterable of items of type T
    Identity
    An Identity is a Function which takes a single object as an input, and simply returns that object.
    If<I,O>
    An If is a Function that conditionally applies one of two functions to a provided input.
    IsEmpty
    A IsEmpty is a KorypheFunction which returns a boolean based on whether or not the input Iterable is empty.
    IterableConcat<I_ITEM>
    An IterableConcat is a KorypheFunction which flattens an Iterable of Iterables by concatenating them.
    IterableFilter<I_ITEM>
    A IterableFilter is a Function that filters items from an Iterable based on a Predicate.
    IterableFunction<I_ITEM,O_ITEM>
    An IterableFunction is a KorypheFunction which lazily applies a supplied Function, or List of Functions to each object in the input Iterable, returning an output Iterable.
    IterableFunction.Builder<I_ITEM>  
    IterableFunction.OutputBuilder<I_ITEM,O_ITEM>  
    LastItem<T>
    A LastItem is a KorypheFunction that returns the last item from a provided Iterable of items of type T
    Length
    A Length is a KorypheFunction that returns the length for a provided object.
    MapFilter<K,V>
    A MapFilter is a Function that filters items from a Map based on a Predicate.
    Multiply
    A Multiply is a Function that takes in two Integers and returns the result of multiplying the first by the second.
    MultiplyBy
    A MultiplyBy is a Function that takes in an Integer and returns the result of multiplying this integer by a pre-configured value.
    NthItem<T>
    A NthItem is a KorypheFunction that returns an item based on user selection, from an Iterable of items of type T
    SetValue
    A SetValue is a Function that takes an input object and returns a set value.
    Size
    A Size is a KorypheFunction which returns the size of a provided Iterable.
    ToArray
    A ToArray is a Function that takes an Object and converts it to a array.
    ToInteger
    A ToInteger is a Function that takes an Object and casts it to an Integer.
    ToList
    A ToList is a Function that takes an Object and converts it to a list.
    ToLong
    A ToLong is a Function that takes an Object and casts it to a Long.
    ToLowerCase
    A ToLowerCase is a Function that takes an Object and performs toLowerCase on it.
    ToNull
    A toNull is a Function that takes an Object and returns null.
    ToSet
    A ToSet is a Function that takes an Object and converts it to a set.
    ToString
    A ToString is a Function that takes in an object (null or otherwise), and calls toString on it.
    ToUpperCase
    A ToUpperCase is a Function that takes an Object and performs toUpperCase on it.
